  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether screening of pregnant women with history of
      previous preterm delivery, once a week, for bacterial vaginosis using VA-SENSE, and treatment
      of positive women will reduce the risk of spontaneous preterm birth. We will compare between
      the effectiveness of once a week screening and once during pregnancy screening.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
